# Severnaya, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Severnaya () is a rural locality (a village) in Oktyabrsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 337 as of 2010. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Severnaya is located 34 km west of Sterlitamak (the district's administrative centre) by road. Oktyabrskoye is the nearest rural locality.
